There are many reseources that cover the more technical details of port scanning and the different types of port scanning. In this guide we are going to the basics. The missing part of this introduction to network basics is the hostmane, DNS record or domain name. It is a reference to the IP address using an easier to remember name. For example what is easier to remember or www.google.com When you type www.google.com into your browser you are directed via the domain name system to on port . The port is done by the browser automatically. If you type https into the browser you go to a different port . As this is the standard port for the encrypted SSL protocol. Here are some common ports that you will find when using a port scanner.
